The subject provides theoretical knowledge on basic principles of haematology and practical training in frequent haematological illnesses, their diagnostics and treatment (haematopoietic malignancies, red cell pathology, coagulation disorders, bone marrow disorders). This is one part of the subject "Internal Diseases".Objectives/eesmärkid:  The purpose of this subject is obtaining knowledge on basic principles of haematology, the symptomatology, diagnostic of haematological illnesses, common principles of their treatment. Hematological diseases include - hematological malignancies, coagulation disorders, red cell disorders, hereditary and acquired bone marrow pathology.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing the course the student 1. Knows the principes of  prevention, diagnostics and treatment of following hematological diseases: hematological cancers, aneemias, coagulation disorders,   disorders related to bone marrow stem cells; 2. Clinical and communication skills     a.	is able to obtain anamnesis covering any potential aspects pertaining to a disease;     b.	is s able to carry out the objective examination of the patient's state of health and fix it in the prescribed medical documentation; 3. Is able to create the primary diagnosis upon clinical symptoms; 4. Clinical skills     a.	is able to chose optikal and reasoned examination methods to diagnose a disease;     b.	is able to interpret the results of diagnostic methods and define the diagnosis;     c.	is able to create suitable treatment strategies.
